This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image classification. It also involves the use of deep neural networks, which suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the use of autoencoders and the focus on discriminative capability suggests that it could belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The use of maximum margin criterion and the focus on enhancing discriminative capability also suggests that it could belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the focus on cross-view image classification suggests that it could belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
